# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Secrets — false positives
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# azure-storage-account-key
# Source: knowledge/mcp-apps/trey-research/src/mcpserver/server/src/db.ts
# Reason: This is the publicly documented Azurite Storage Emulator default key
#         (`Eby8vdM02xNOcqFlqUwJPLlmEtlCDXJ1OUzFT50uSRZ6IFsuFq2UVErCz4I6tq/K1SZFPTOtr/KBHBeksoGMGw==`).
#         It is the well-known development credential Microsoft publishes for the local
#         Azure Storage Emulator. It cannot authenticate to any real Azure resource.
#         The file is in the knowledge-base repo (MCP sample app reference), not in
#         deployed product code.
# Reference: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/storage/common/storage-use-azurite#well-known-storage-account-and-key
# Workflow also skips `knowledge/` from Trivy scan (sdap-ci.yml); this entry is a
# defense-in-depth backstop in case the skip-dirs config changes.
azure-storage-account-key

