# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Deferred — build-tooling transitives (not in runtime bundles)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The CVEs below all trace to transitive dev/build dependencies inside the
# PCF tooling tree (eslint, glob, rimraf, pcf-scripts). They are:
#   - Not in any runtime bundle that ships to users.
#   - DoS / ReDoS classes — require attacker-controlled pattern input. CI build
#     context has no untrusted glob input, so exploitability is effectively zero.
#   - Parent-pinned (consumers explicitly require ^3.x). Forcing a transitive
#     bump via `overrides` would conflict with typescript-eslint's ^9.x branch.
# Re-evaluate when parent packages (eslint, glob, pcf-scripts) ship patched
# releases that consume the fixed versions naturally.

# CVE-2026-26996 — minimatch 3.1.2 HIGH (DoS via crafted glob)
# Source: src/client/pcf/SpeDocumentViewer/package-lock.json (transitive: eslint, glob)
CVE-2026-26996

# CVE-2026-27903 — minimatch 3.1.2 HIGH (DoS)
